Police and firefighters are on high alert in the Johannesburg CBD after a scrapyard was set alight in Jeppestown late on Monday afternoon. This, as part of ongoing protests in the area. Protesting residents gathered earlier to call on foreign nationals to leave. Several protesters told News24 they wanted foreigners to leave the area, claiming that they were behind drug-dealing in the area. WATCH | Man arrested in Tshwane CBD for attempting to block intersection A man was arrested in the Tshwane CBD on Monday after parking his car in the middle of an intersection.
